{
  "id": "gedit_python_class_refactor",
  "app": "gedit",
  "task": "/home/user/Documents/calculator.py currently contains three standalone functions (`add`, `subtract`, `multiply`) followed by demo `print()` calls.\n\nRefactor it into a class-based implementation in the same file:\n- Define a class `Calculator` at the top of the file with three methods (taking `self` as the first parameter): `def add(self, a, b): return a + b`, `def subtract(self, a, b): return a - b`, `def multiply(self, a, b): return a * b`. The arithmetic return lines (`return a + b`, `return a - b`, `return a * b`) must all still appear in the file.\n- Below the class, instantiate it with `calc = Calculator()` and call all three methods in `print()` statements using the same arguments as the original demo section.\n\nThe final file must be at least 18 lines long and must still live at /home/user/Documents/calculator.py.",
  "env": {
    "files": [
      {
        "filename": "calculator.py",
        "sandbox_path": "/home/user/Documents/calculator.py"
      }
    ]
  },
  "verification": [
    {
      "command": "check-file-exists /home/user/Documents/calculator.py",
      "key": "exists",
      "expected": true,
      "description": "calculator.py exists"
    },
    {
      "command": "check-file-contains /home/user/Documents/calculator.py \"class Calculator:\"",
      "key": "contains",
      "expected": true,
      "description": "File defines class Calculator"
    },
    {
      "command": "check-file-contains /home/user/Documents/calculator.py \"def add(self\"",
      "key": "contains",
      "expected": true,
      "description": "add is a method on the class"
    },
    {
      "command": "check-file-contains /home/user/Documents/calculator.py \"def subtract(self\"",
      "key": "contains",
      "expected": true,
      "description": "subtract is a method on the class"
    },
    {
      "command": "check-file-contains /home/user/Documents/calculator.py \"def multiply(self\"",
      "key": "contains",
      "expected": true,
      "description": "multiply is a method on the class"
    },
    {
      "command": "check-file-contains /home/user/Documents/calculator.py \"return a + b\"",
      "key": "contains",
      "expected": true,
      "description": "add logic preserved"
    },
    {
      "command": "check-file-contains /home/user/Documents/calculator.py \"return a - b\"",
      "key": "contains",
      "expected": true,
      "description": "subtract logic preserved"
    },
    {
      "command": "check-file-contains /home/user/Documents/calculator.py \"return a * b\"",
      "key": "contains",
      "expected": true,
      "description": "multiply logic preserved"
